Sec. 72.021. DETERMINATION OF INFESTATION. (a) If an
accredited entomologist finds or knows that the larvae of the Mexican
fruit fly exist on premises within a quarantined area, the
entomologist shall certify the fact of the infestation to the
department.
(b) The department shall determine whether the infestation
exists and the extent of the infestation. The department may refer
the issue to the citrus quarantine advisory committee of any county
in which the premises are located.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1166, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

